build: Enhance Nuitka compiler with LTO and UPX plugin
- Enable Link Time Optimization (LTO) in the Python to C++ compiler (Nuitka) - Add a UPX plugin in Nuitka compiler - Leave a note about potential failure of UPX plugin when file size exceeds 768MB
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: refactor Dockerfile for optional Nuitka compilation
- Changed the target in the docker publish workflow from 'final' to 'final_nuitka' - Removed the Nuitka compilation in Dockerfile and added a base stage - Reordered and organized Dockerfile with comments to differentiate between stages - Changed build stage, installing build-essential only, removed specific patchelf - Removed Nuitka installation from requirements - Added a cleanup process removing all byte-compiled Python files - Added stages 'prepare_final', 'compile_nuitka', 'report_nuitka', 'final_nuitka', and redefined the 'final' stage - Accommodated the changes in Docker building with either Nuitka compiled or normal Python execution as options - Readability and maintainability of Dockerfile improved by reorganizing and commenting stages
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore(Nuitka): refactor Dockerfile for improved package handling
- Add nofollow imports for certain packages (torch, numba, xformers, triton, llvmlite) in the Dockerfile configuration - Copy additional site-packages (torch, numba, xformers, triton, llvmlite) from the build stage to `/app` in Dockerfile - Remove the `--skip-torch-cuda-test` flag from the ENTRYPOINT command - Change the copy order in the final stage of Dockerfile, adding `stable-diffusion-webui` to `/app` before copying local dependencies to `/home/$UID/.local`.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

ci: implement new automated GitHub actions
- Add a new GitHub action to automatically approve and merge PRs if they are created by 'jim60105' in the 'jim60105/docker-stable-diffusion-webui' repository. - Introduce a new GitHub action for weekly automated updating of submodules, with PRs to be automatically labeled for merging.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

feat: refactor command options
- Add comments about the pre-configured command options in the Docker service command section. - Include new command options `--xformers`, `--no-half-vae`, `--opt-sdp-attention`, `--opt-sdp-no-mem-attention`, and `--opt-channelslast` for the Docker service. - Remove the `--xformers` and `--enable-insecure-extension-access` options from the Docker service command. - Re-add the `--enable-insecure-extension-access` option later in the Docker service command list with additional advice on usage. - Provide a reference to the full list of command-line arguments and settings for the stable diffusion web UI in the comments.
Signed-off-by: 陳鈞 <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore: fix /app/scripts/*.py not loaded
